pullsbody:
Notable changes:
- Performance benefit from connection pooling, if the same `TreeherderClient` instance is re-used for multiple requests.
- The separate `host` and `protocol` arguments have been combined into a single `server_url` argument.

See here for more details:
https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1286240
pull_commit_message:
Update to treeherder-client 3.0.0

Notable changes:
* Performance benefit from connection pooling, if the same
`TreeherderClient` instance is re-used for multiple requests.
* The separate `host` and `protocol` arguments have been combined into a
single `server_url` argument.

See here for more details:
https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1286240

pulltitle: Better handling for perf job failures
pullsbody:
The job guid is now comprised of a hash of the revision and perfdata.
This helps treeherder understand if we are reposting the same job data.

The job posting logic is also updated to continue processing other
builds even if there is a failure posting the current job.

pulltitle: Store logs in S3 and report them to treeherder (#116)
pullsbody:
This adds support for posting the logs for a test run to S3 and
treeherder. Both the unit test log and gecko log (what's actually output
from the Firefox session) are included.

Logs are stored under the following path:
    `http://<S3_bucket>/<repo>/<revision>/<guid>/`

@nnethercote Can you take a look?

pulltitle: Use a single mozlog for each test (#116)
pullsbody:
This unifies the log used by BenchTester, BenchTest, MarionetteTest, and
test_memory_usage. It defaults to mach-style output and switches over to
using "raw" logs (aka structured logging) if a logfile is specified.

This gives a much more thorough test log as the output from the marionette test is included.

@nnethercote can you take a look?

pulltitle: Lookup full revision for try builds (#111)
pullsbody:
|mozdownload| now requires the full length revision when requesting a
try build. TryBuilder is updated to look that up if a short revision is
provided. Additionally the 12 character limit is removed when requesting
a try build. Tests have been updated for both styles.

pull_commit_message:
Handle multiple instances of the same process type

Normalize process names to include a process number if there are
multiple instances.

Example mapping:
  [ "Main" => "Main",
    "Web Content (123)" => "Web Content",
    "Web Content (234)" => "Web Content 2",
    "Web Content (345)" => "Web Content 3" ]

The first instance of the process name excludes the number so as to
avoid breaking graph generation for the AWSY website which expects names
without numbers.

pull_commit_message: [html] Fixup zoom out button and page centering
Use cursor:pointer for [zoom out] button.

Use colors from http://colorbrewer2.org/.

They're not great, but they're a lot better than what we had.  As an additional bonus, each of the colors is easily nameable ({light,dark} {blue,green,red,orange,purple}).
Use friendly names for plotted lines.
Don't center the graph legend.
Renaming legend items.
Use a power of 2 for the y-axis tick interval.
Don't display decimal points on axis labels.
Don't display day of week in x-axis label.
Changing the axis labels I'd previously forgotten to change.
